  "root_text": {
    "iti72:0.1": "Itivuttaka 72 ",
    "iti72:0.2": "Tikanipāta ",
    "iti72:0.3": "Tatiyavagga ",
    "iti72:0.4": "Nissaraṇiyasutta ",
    "iti72:1.1": "Vuttañhetaṁ bhagavatā vuttamarahatāti me sutaṁ: ",
    "iti72:2.1": "“Tisso imā, bhikkhave, nissaraṇiyā dhātuyo. ",
    "iti72:2.2": "Katamā tisso? ",
    "iti72:2.3": "Kāmānametaṁ nissaraṇaṁ yadidaṁ nekkhammaṁ, rūpānametaṁ nissaraṇaṁ yadidaṁ āruppaṁ, yaṁ kho pana kiñci bhūtaṁ saṅkhataṁ paṭiccasamuppannaṁ nirodho tassa nissaraṇaṁ—",
    "iti72:2.4": "imā kho, bhikkhave, tisso nissaraṇiyā dhātuyo”ti. ",
    "iti72:2.5": "Etamatthaṁ bhagavā avoca. ",
    "iti72:2.6": "Tatthetaṁ iti vuccati: ",
    "iti72:3.1": "“Kāmanissaraṇaṁ ñatvā, ",
    "iti72:3.2": "rūpānañca atikkamaṁ; ",
    "iti72:3.3": "Sabbasaṅkhārasamathaṁ, ",
    "iti72:3.4": "phusaṁ ātāpi sabbadā. ",
    "iti72:4.1": "Sa ve sammaddaso bhikkhu, ",
    "iti72:4.2": "yato tattha vimuccati; ",
    "iti72:4.3": "Abhiññāvosito santo, ",
    "iti72:4.4": "sa ve yogātigo munī”ti. ",
    "iti72:5.1": "Ayampi attho vutto bhagavatā, iti me sutanti. ",
    "iti72:5.2": "Tatiyaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "iti72:0.1": "So It Was Said 72 ",
    "iti72:0.2": "The Book of the Threes ",
    "iti72:0.3": "Chapter Three ",
    "iti72:0.4": "Elements of Escape ",
    "iti72:1.1": "This was said by the Buddha, the Perfected One: that is what I heard. ",
    "iti72:2.1": "“Mendicants, there are these three elements of escape. ",
    "iti72:2.2": "What three? ",
    "iti72:2.3": "Renunciation is the escape from sensual pleasures. Formlessness is the escape from form. Cessation is the escape from whatever is created, conditioned, and dependently originated. ",
    "iti72:2.4": "These are the three elements of escape.” ",
    "iti72:2.5": "The Buddha spoke this matter. ",
    "iti72:2.6": "On this it is said: ",
    "iti72:3.1": "“Knowing the escape from sensuality, ",
    "iti72:3.2": "and form’s transcendence, ",
    "iti72:3.3": "one always keen touches ",
    "iti72:3.4": "the stilling of all activities. ",
    "iti72:4.1": "That mendicant sees rightly, ",
    "iti72:4.2": "and when freed in regards to that, ",
    "iti72:4.3": "that peaceful sage, with perfect insight, ",
    "iti72:4.4": "has truly slipped their yoke.” ",
    "iti72:5.1": "This too is a matter that was spoken by the Blessed One: that is what I heard. "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "iti72:2.1": "nissaraṇiyā → nissāraṇīyā (an5.200:1 [200. Nissāraṇīyasutta]) "
  },
